# Claude Code — local state stays ignored, but project slash COMMANDS are
# versioned (they encode project doctrine, e.g. /triage-wave's >30%-FP gate).
# NOTE: `.claude/*` (not `.claude/`) so the negation below can re-include the
# commands dir — git never descends into a fully-ignored directory.
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
tmpclaude-*

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Scratch artifacts (root-level analysis output)
/out*.sarif
/perf_stderr.txt

